Free Valet Parking

  for Patients and their Visitors

   How to use valet parking at the Clinical Center: Drive directly to the
   main south entrance of the Clinical Center. A valet parking attendant
   will give you a claim ticket. The attendant will park your vehicle in
   valet parking spaces in lot 10H near the main entrance.

   Where to get your car: Show your claim ticket to the parking attendant
   outside the Clinical Centers south lobby. The attendant will bring your
   car to the Clinical Centers south entrance driveway. Make sure to have
   your claim ticket validated by the parking validation desk near
   admissions.

   When valet service is available: Monday through Friday, 7 a.m. to 10
   p.m. (except Federal holidays)

   Cost: This service is free to patients and their visitors.

   Note: Patients and patients' visitors will still be able to self-park
   their vehicles in the P3 level of the garage.
